race.comment: This isn't strong, and the Waterhouse-Bott-trained STATE SECRET (5) gets his chance on debut. Has been fitted out with two Randwick trials and is expected to jump and run from the inside barrier. The yard has scratched the stablemate. The late betting will be key. BOLD ALLIANCE (10) brings a 1.8L defeat from Hawkesbury when she led. Uses the inside gate and has a handy 2kg claim. She's got plenty of upside and is a serious player. The local SHUTTERING (12) is third-up for Pepper after the switch from a top Sydney stable. Has an awkward gate but has an in-form rider aboard. Settled too far back here last time after a promising first-up effort. Has each way claims. No surprise to see quick improvement from the Ible-trained ALAMAGAN (1), who had no luck at Kembla Grange on debut. He was expected to need it regardless, and he maps to get every chance.
